to the editor a feb 6 news article says a study of 293 american men infected with hiv revealed that only 29 percent knew they were infected shocking figures like these will never turn around until we carry out universal routine hiv testing confidential and complete name reporting to public health officials and mandatory partner notification we now routinely test for hiv in all blood donors and federal prisoners as well as all of the military all overseas state department employees and most insurance policy subscribers confidentiality has never been breached within the public health system the control and spread of this lethal virus will stop only when hiv is no longer treated as the only secret disease in the history of modern medicine sanford f kuvin md palm beach fla feb 6 2001 the writer is chairman of the sanford kuvin center for infectious and tropical diseases hebrew university of jerusalem

